ext-decoration:none\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"line-height:7.25pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif\"><span style=\"color:#161616\">SCHOOL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></b></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></u><br />\n<span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"line-height:16.4267px\"><span style=\"color:#d1383b\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:-0.25pt\"><strong>INDIA</strong></span></span><strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#d1383b\">CHINA&nbsp;<span style=\"letter-spacing:-0.25pt\">INSTITUTE</span></span></strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:start; padding:5px 0px 0px 5px\"><span style=\"font-size:13px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:arial\"><font color=\"#e82e21\"><b>GRACE HOU</b></font><br />\n<font color=\"#000000\"><font style=\"font-size:10px\"><b>DEPUTY DIRECTOR&nbsp;</b></font></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\n<span style=\"font-size:10px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-family:arial\"><font color=\"#666666\">79 5th Ave, Suite 1643</font><br style=\"color:#666666\" />\n<span style=\"color:#666666\">NEW YORK, NY 10003</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\n<span style=\"font-size:10px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#666666\"><span style=\"font-family:arial\"><u>houg<a href=\"https://www.newschool.edu/marketing-communication/email-signature.html#\" style=\"color:#666666\" target=\"_blank\">@newschool.edu</a></u><br />\n<span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\">T</span></span>&nbsp;212-229-6812X3344 /&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\">T</span></span>&nbsp;212-627-0369</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n"},"field_event_mode":"","field_event_language":"English","field_event_record":true,"field_event_category":"Talk","field_time_zone":"America/New_York","field_event_website":{"uri":"https://www.indiachinainstitute.org/event/china-and-india-in-africa/"},"field_registration":true,"field_event_venue":"Zoom Webinar","field_description":{"processed":"<p dir=\"ltr\">We are pleased to invite you to a thought-provoking discussion that explores China in Africa paradigm in a comparative perspective with India.</p>\n\n<p><meta charset=\"UTF-8\" /></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">While much attention has been centered on China in Africa and Global China as a lens through which to examine changing patterns of investment and infrastructure in Africa, this panel puts the China in Africa paradigm in a comparative perspective with India, which has longstanding commercial and trade ties with East and South Africa.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This online panel,&nbsp;co-sponsored with the Heilbroner Center for Capitalism Studies of The New School,&nbsp;will assess Indian and Chinese engagements in Africa through the lens of technology transfers, skills upgrading, educational exchanges, and knowledge flows. Participants will explore patterns of expertise and technology transfer, higher education partnerships, cross-border research collaborations, and supply chains, among other forms of engagement between Chinese and Indian organizations with African counterparts<br />\n<br />\nRegister&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.indiachinainstitute.org/event/china-and-india-in-africa/\">here.</a></p>\n"}}},"context":{}}